1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 18=

3
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:46,080
Zhanqiao.

4
00:01:47,080 --> 00:01:47,760
Mr. Fan.

5
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:49,790
Are you going to keep
the updates coming or not?

6
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:51,760
Can Gu Yan even keep writing this?

7
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:53,800
Just give me a straight answer.

8
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:55,200
Well,

9
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:57,239
(Drunk Old Friend, Chapter 215)
if there is still no response from you,

10
00:01:57,240 --> 00:01:58,960
we will have to go with the backup plan.

11
00:01:59,440 --> 00:02:01,640
We will release a statement then.

12
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:03,520
We will say

13
00:02:04,044 --> 00:02:05,120
it's due to health reasons

14
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,560
or something else.

15
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:09,200
But first, you have to find him.

16
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:11,440
Before you release anything,

17
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:13,200
you need to give Gu Yan
a heads-up, right?

18
00:02:13,288 --> 00:02:15,088
Otherwise, if I put out
the statement here

19
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:16,880
and he suddenly shows up,

20
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:19,000
wouldn't that make us look ridiculous?

21
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:19,740
(Send)

22
00:02:20,488 --> 00:02:22,200
(Email sent)
Are you even listening to me?

23
00:02:23,760 --> 00:02:24,320
Mr. Fan.

24
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:26,600
Well, I...

25
00:02:26,888 --> 00:02:28,790
I've already sent
the manuscript to the editor.

26
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:30,800
Gu Yan updated?

27
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:33,040
When did that happen?

28
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:34,240
Just now.

29
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:35,240
Bye.

30
00:02:48,620 --> 00:02:52,140
(Chapter 215: Hidden Depths)

31
00:02:57,977 --> 00:02:59,311
Why did you want to see me?

32
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:02,480
Why not let me go up?

33
00:03:03,777 --> 00:03:04,360
Someone there?

34
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:06,160
I was worried you might not leave.

35
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:06,760
What is it?

36
00:03:07,311 --> 00:03:08,280
Here's the situation.

37
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:11,240
Gu Yan had been
stalling and not updating,

38
00:03:11,311 --> 00:03:12,930
and now suddenly he turned something in

39
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:14,920
without any warning.

40
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:17,560
Lin Zhanqiao suddenly sent me the draft.

41
00:03:17,760 --> 00:03:19,760
We have never been able to reach Gu Yan.

42
00:03:19,844 --> 00:03:20,755
I asked Lin Zhanqiao

43
00:03:20,777 --> 00:03:22,880
about the follow-up update
plan for Drunk Old Friend,

44
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:24,240
and she hesitated.

45
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:27,280
Had it really come from Gu Yan,

46
00:03:27,290 --> 00:03:29,260
she wouldn't have
been reacting like that, right?

47
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,440
She wrote it for him?

48
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:33,280
No, come here. Take a look first.

49
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:33,920
Take a look.

50
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:34,960
It is not good?

51
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:37,400
It is not that it is bad.
It is too good.

52
00:03:37,644 --> 00:03:39,960
So good that even ten
Lin Zhanqiaos could not write it.

53
00:03:44,044 --> 00:03:44,955
What do you think?

54
00:03:50,720 --> 00:03:51,760
You mean He Han...

55
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:53,600
He stepped in to save the day.

56
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:54,680
Possible?

57
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:57,640
He Han was writing updates last night,

58
00:03:57,640 --> 00:03:59,360
but he should have
been working on his own.

59
00:04:04,777 --> 00:04:06,066
I will ask him tomorrow.

60
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:08,800
If it really is He Han ghostwriting,

61
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:12,680
why do we not just pair He Han

62
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:13,780
and Lin Zhanqiao together?

63
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,320
My plan

64
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:16,800
is to let He Han write for now

65
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:19,480
and still use Gu Yan's name.

66
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:21,200
When readers start to feel

67
00:04:21,220 --> 00:04:22,760
the updates are
getting better and better,

68
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:23,960
more and more engaging...

69
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:24,800
Of course,

70
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:26,520
we will give it a push as well.

71
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:29,240
Then, at the right time,

72
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:31,520
we reveal the truth.

73
00:04:32,266 --> 00:04:33,200
What do you think?

74
00:04:34,288 --> 00:04:37,400
Isn't this story of turning the tide
and rekindling a past relationship

75
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:39,560
compelling and moving?

76
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:42,400
What about me?

77
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:44,640
Drunk Old Friend

78
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:47,760
will become something shared
between you and Lin Zhanqiao.

79
00:04:48,844 --> 00:04:49,600
How great is that?

80
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:51,240
You will get a top-tier IP for free.

81
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:54,080
Later, I will acquire
her company as well.

82
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:55,080
You will

83
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:57,000
be one of the shareholders.

84
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:01,440
Wait for my news.

85
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:05,160
Go back and wait for my news.

86
00:05:05,888 --> 00:05:07,355
I will take a look at the draft first.

87
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:47,440
He Han.

88
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:55,960
Where's the update?

89
00:05:58,520 --> 00:05:59,240
You are so early.

90
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:00,840
It is done.

91
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:01,920
Just a few words left.

92
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:03,120
Have you eaten?

93
00:06:03,130 --> 00:06:04,740
Why not go downstairs
and grab something?

94
00:06:04,755 --> 00:06:06,422
After you eat, you will receive it.

95
00:06:06,533 --> 00:06:07,720
It will not even be 9 AM yet.

96
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:08,860
The editors will not be at work.

97
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:09,640
You send it to them,

98
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:11,800
and they will see it as
soon as they come in. Perfect.

99
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:13,240
Just a few words left, right?

100
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:13,720
Alright.

101
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:15,240
I will wait here for you to finish.

102
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:17,320
Sure, sit for a bit.

103
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:18,600
I will be done soon.

104
00:06:21,311 --> 00:06:23,360
Gu Yan submitted right
at the deadline yesterday.

105
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:24,200
You know that, right?

106
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:24,720
Really?

107
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:27,300
Do you believe it?

108
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:29,080
Yeah, why not?

109
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:32,420
Which author does not
submit at the last second?

110
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:33,444
Nothing unusual.

111
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:35,800
The draft was
personally edited by Lin Zhanqiao

112
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:36,800
and sent to Dingqi.

113
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:37,960
It was not forwarded through

114
00:06:37,960 --> 00:06:39,800
the assigned editor like usual.

115
00:06:40,280 --> 00:06:41,644
Didn't you say it was last-minute?

116
00:06:41,650 --> 00:06:43,340
Lin Zhanqiao probably got anxious
and handled it herself.

117
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:43,990
Nothing unusual.

118
00:06:46,866 --> 00:06:49,040
So last night,
when you were writing so intensely,

119
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:50,960
were you working
on your own Shattered Six States

120
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:52,800
or Gu Yan's Drunk Old Friend?

121
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:55,000
Why is his update finished,

122
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,440
but yours is not?

123
00:06:56,640 --> 00:06:58,160
You don't have much saved up either.

124
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:02,360
There is only one chapter.

125
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:05,720
What if Gu Yan
stops writing from now on?

126
00:07:05,888 --> 00:07:06,777
What will you do?

127
00:07:06,844 --> 00:07:07,888
Will you help or not?

128
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:09,200
If you don't help,

129
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:10,880
then helping this
one time means nothing.

130
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:12,800
If you do help,

131
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:13,240
fine.

132
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:14,920
Under what name will you help?

133
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:16,600
Under your name, He Han,

134
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:18,080
or under Gu Yan's name?

135
00:07:18,760 --> 00:07:19,920
I believe you would not want

136
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:21,040
your name and Gu Yan's name

137
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:22,680
to appear together.

138
00:07:22,888 --> 00:07:23,688
So what then?

139
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:25,720
Continue under a new name?

140
00:07:26,866 --> 00:07:27,890
I never thought about it.

141
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:38,280
If you write under your own name,

142
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:39,720
I get a cut.

143
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:42,200
If you write under Gu Yan's name,

144
00:07:42,440 --> 00:07:44,080
it has nothing to do with me.

145
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:46,480
So if you want to
keep being the good guy

146
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:47,600
in front of Lin Zhanqiao,

147
00:07:48,044 --> 00:07:49,760
then the one you are letting down is me.

148
00:07:51,822 --> 00:07:52,720
That makes sense.

149
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:56,000
If you are going to
keep helping Lin Zhanqiao

150
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,880
ghostwrite Drunk Old Friend,

151
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:00,480
I will go negotiate terms with Dingqi.

152
00:08:03,777 --> 00:08:05,555
You have already spoken with Mr. Fan?

153
00:08:05,840 --> 00:08:06,920
He is prepared

154
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:09,080
for all possible situations.

155
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:11,240
No need. It's nothing serious.

156
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:13,555
- Just a temporary favor.
- You should talk to Lin Zhanqiao.

157
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:15,400
Talk about what?

158
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:16,990
You can't bring yourself to do it?

159
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:18,040
Fine, I'll go.

160
00:08:18,511 --> 00:08:19,840
- Hurry up and write.
- Don't.

161
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,120
Open your laptop and start writing.

162
00:08:22,520 --> 00:08:22,960
Hurry up.

163
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:32,880
On the seventh night,

164
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,360
a heart-pounding chase...

165
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:36,160
Zhangzhu,

166
00:08:36,680 --> 00:08:37,760
has Gu Yan updated?

167
00:08:38,920 --> 00:08:39,280
Yeah?

168
00:08:40,040 --> 00:08:40,360
Good.

169
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:41,320
That's great.

170
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:44,200
Ms. Lin didn't go home yesterday.

171
00:08:44,955 --> 00:08:46,080
She didn't change clothes.

172
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:48,240
No wonder.

173
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:50,200
I was wondering why
I didn't see her this morning.

174
00:08:50,210 --> 00:08:51,440
I thought she had already left.

175
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:52,400
So you don't know

176
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:53,720
why she didn't go home?

177
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:54,560
No idea.

178
00:08:56,044 --> 00:08:57,800
The update went up five minutes ago.

179
00:08:57,810 --> 00:08:58,800
You've already read it?

180
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:00,400
I read it yesterday.

181
00:09:00,410 --> 00:09:01,760
When she sent it to Dingqi Platform,

182
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:03,310
didn't she also send
a copy to the group?

183
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:04,480
I saw it right away.

184
00:09:05,266 --> 00:09:07,440
Even though Gu Yan
caused us some trouble this time,

185
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:10,200
we have to admit

186
00:09:10,755 --> 00:09:12,120
that the quality of this update

187
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:13,400
is really high.

188
00:09:14,555 --> 00:09:16,066
Isn't it even better than before?

189
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:18,120
I think

190
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:21,000
he knew today's chapter would blow up,

191
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,440
so he made Ms. Lin wait like that.

192
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:23,880
Now that it's out,

193
00:09:24,066 --> 00:09:25,320
Ms. Lin can't say anything.

194
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:27,800
The question

195
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:30,320
is whether he can keep this level going.

196
00:10:24,260 --> 00:10:27,020
(Dingqi Reading Platform real-time data:
Shattered Six States, Drunk Old Friend)

197
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:37,020
(Chapter 215: Hidden Depths)

198
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:48,000
Zhangzhu.

199
00:10:48,977 --> 00:10:50,880
This isn't the one
from the group yesterday.

200
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:52,040
No.

201
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:54,040
I don't know why either.

202
00:10:54,088 --> 00:10:55,990
Was there something
wrong with yesterday's version?

203
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:34,560
I'm sorry.

204
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:38,400
In the end, we didn't use your draft.

205
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:48,320
I'll come see you at noon.

206
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:50,200
I'll explain it in person.

207
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:52,160
No need to explain.

208
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:22,440
Ms. Lin, did you send the wrong update?

209
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:24,880
No.

210
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,600
But the one you sent

211
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:28,440
wasn't the one
Mr. He Han wrote yesterday.

212
00:12:31,177 --> 00:12:32,320
That was written by Gu Yan.

213
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:33,640
Gu Yan?

214
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:36,240
When did he write it?

215
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:39,440
He sent it to me last night.

216
00:12:41,860 --> 00:12:44,820
(Ten Hours Ago)

217
00:13:04,140 --> 00:13:08,620
(Chapter 215: Hidden Depths)

218
00:13:11,660 --> 00:13:14,700
(He Han, Gu Yan)

219
00:13:41,460 --> 00:13:43,620
(00:10 AM, Lin Zhanqiao: Rong,
previous draft void. Use this version)

220
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:49,960
So you didn't go home last night

221
00:13:49,960 --> 00:13:51,622
because you were handling his update.

222
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:58,400
I thought it through.

223
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:01,320
It made more sense to let
Dingqi Platform publish his version.

224
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:07,000
After all, it's his work.

225
00:14:07,760 --> 00:14:08,200
So,

226
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:10,760
we should use his content.

227
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:15,440
But the whole mess now

228
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:17,160
was caused by Gu Yan himself.

229
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:17,720
Shouldn't he

230
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:18,600
at least face

231
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:19,800
some consequences?

232
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:21,760
Why does it feel like nothing happened?

233
00:14:22,577 --> 00:14:24,444
What about the people
who worried about him

234
00:14:24,488 --> 00:14:26,222
and covered for him? What did they get?

235
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:30,040
I think this isn't fair.

236
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:32,400
He probably had a rough night, too.

237
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:36,360
He knows he can't afford to fail.

238
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:38,920
So, in the end,

239
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,640
he still submitted it.

240
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:49,520
Does Mr. He Han know?

241
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:56,640
He knows now.

242
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:11,120
Lin Zhanqiao

243
00:15:11,280 --> 00:15:12,920
didn't use your update.

244
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:16,360
Right now,

245
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:18,840
they're still using Gu Yan's.

246
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:21,000
Fan said

247
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:23,760
Lin Zhanqiao made
a last-minute decision this morning

248
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:26,560
to replace your update at Dingqi

249
00:15:26,560 --> 00:15:28,840
and use Gu Yan's version.

250
00:15:35,010 --> 00:15:35,670
Fan.

251
00:15:37,266 --> 00:15:38,666
Yeah, he's right here with me.

252
00:15:38,977 --> 00:15:39,960
I'll put him on speaker.

253
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:40,480
It's on.

254
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:42,000
He Han,

255
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:44,080
about this matter,

256
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:45,480
- I need to explain.
- Take it.

257
00:15:45,920 --> 00:15:47,560
They didn't use the one you wrote.

258
00:15:48,160 --> 00:15:49,760
It really wasn't my decision.

259
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:52,280
I kept trying to persuade Lin Zhanqiao.

260
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:53,000
You see,

261
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:54,440
before ten,

262
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:56,360
I was still calling her.

263
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:59,240
But she insisted on protecting Gu Yan.

264
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:00,800
I couldn't do anything.

265
00:16:01,333 --> 00:16:03,040
I know if we're talking about quality,

266
00:16:03,040 --> 00:16:04,760
yours was surely better.

267
00:16:05,280 --> 00:16:06,800
I also wanted something impactful

268
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:08,160
to boost traffic, you know?

269
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:11,440
But Lin Zhanqiao wouldn't listen.

270
00:16:11,933 --> 00:16:13,600
She even used
the contract to restrict me.

271
00:16:14,920 --> 00:16:15,560
Yesterday,

272
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:18,120
was it she who asked you to help?

273
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:20,600
Alright, that's enough.

274
00:16:20,880 --> 00:16:21,955
He can't hear you anymore.

275
00:16:25,040 --> 00:16:26,200
Acting on impulse

276
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:29,360
means you have to be ready
to walk away disappointed.

277
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:32,280
He isn't saying anything,

278
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:34,840
but he's surely upset.

279
00:16:35,960 --> 00:16:38,320
As for him and Lin Zhanqiao,

280
00:16:38,511 --> 00:16:40,466
whether their
reconciliation is real or not,

281
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:42,080
I'd say

282
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:43,120
it ends here.

283
00:17:06,280 --> 00:17:07,600
Mr. Fan, you're looking for me?

284
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:09,955
Have we signed
the contract with Chenxing?

285
00:17:10,360 --> 00:17:12,160
They've already signed and sent it over.

286
00:17:12,320 --> 00:17:13,911
We haven't signed and returned it.

287
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:15,280
Good.

288
00:17:15,577 --> 00:17:16,600
Then, don't sign yet.

289
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:19,200
Wait for my word.

290
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:21,920
Hold it for now.

291
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:32,680
You still couldn't resist

292
00:17:32,777 --> 00:17:34,377
writing that update for Lin Zhanqiao.

293
00:17:34,555 --> 00:17:35,920
You keep coming to me because you

294
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:38,000
want to sign with me
as an online fiction author, right?

295
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:39,822
If my first work stops updating

296
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:41,440
and ends up with a bad reputation,

297
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:43,360
that won't be good for you either.

298
00:17:43,844 --> 00:17:44,777
It's fine with me.

299
00:17:44,955 --> 00:17:46,880
I believe this
is Lin Zhanqiao's responsibility.

300
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:48,640
She didn't treat her author properly.

301
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:50,520
If you sign with me,

302
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:52,222
this is how I'll explain it for you.

303
00:17:52,733 --> 00:17:54,380
You really dislike
Lin Zhanqiao that much?

304
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:55,720
It's not about disliking her.

305
00:17:55,822 --> 00:17:58,240
It's about perspective.
I will protect my authors.

306
00:17:59,120 --> 00:17:59,920
For me,

307
00:18:00,155 --> 00:18:01,390
it's not about right or wrong.

308
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:04,000
It's only about us versus them.
If you entrust yourself to me,

309
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:05,640
I'll fight to protect you

310
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:06,720
until the very end.

311
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:09,400
Every boss says that.

312
00:18:11,120 --> 00:18:12,120
I do what I say.

313
00:18:13,288 --> 00:18:14,560
Today, you go back to Chenxing

314
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:16,240
and keep working with Lin Zhanqiao.

315
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:18,680
Your relationship will ease for a while.

316
00:18:18,755 --> 00:18:20,600
But in the end,
you will still come to me.

317
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:22,400
Because she will disappoint you again.

318
00:18:22,880 --> 00:18:23,600
After a few times,

319
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:24,920
you will believe what I said.

320
00:18:25,755 --> 00:18:26,560
I will not leave.

321
00:18:26,711 --> 00:18:28,080
I will be here waiting for you.

322
00:18:38,977 --> 00:18:41,177
Do you know you put
a lot of pressure on people?

323
00:18:43,933 --> 00:18:46,000
To get things done,
there has to be some pressure.

324
00:18:46,320 --> 00:18:47,480
On yourself and on others.

325
00:18:47,822 --> 00:18:49,311
I don't think it is a bad thing.

326
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:50,755
It is just taking the initiative.

327
00:18:58,488 --> 00:18:59,555
See you in Shanghai.

328
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:14,760
Ms. Lin, the average subscriptions
for Drunk Old Friend this week

329
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:16,533
have increased
from the previous baseline.

330
00:19:16,540 --> 00:19:17,640
It should be because this part

331
00:19:17,640 --> 00:19:19,088
has entered a more intense phase.

332
00:19:19,480 --> 00:19:20,160
So, I guess,

333
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:21,680
we made it through this safely.

334
00:19:22,080 --> 00:19:22,480
Got it.

335
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:25,480
Then, I will head back.

336
00:19:47,660 --> 00:19:49,060
(Zhanqiao)

337
00:19:53,420 --> 00:19:55,780
(Zhanqiao)

338
00:20:06,180 --> 00:20:08,100
(Gu Yan: On the way back to Shanghai.
Can I take you out for a meal?)

339
00:20:11,940 --> 00:20:13,500
(These past few days, I lost control.)

340
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:16,460
(About our relationship,
I was too anxious.)

341
00:20:16,460 --> 00:20:17,820
(I felt like you might
leave me at any moment.)

342
00:20:31,260 --> 00:20:32,620
(Gu Yan: On the way back to Shanghai.
Can I take you out for a meal?)

343
00:20:32,620 --> 00:20:34,110
(These past few days, I lost control.)

344
00:20:34,120 --> 00:20:35,890
(About our relationship,
I was too anxious.)

345
00:20:35,933 --> 00:20:37,620
(I felt like you might
leave me at any moment.)

346
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:54,422
Why did you come to
my office during work hours?

347
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:59,280
I cannot sit in my office.

348
00:20:59,280 --> 00:21:00,560
I cannot calmly

349
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:01,320
face my boss.

350
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:04,400
I know you must be
just as angry as I am, right?

351
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:07,560
What is there to be angry about?

352
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:08,800
It is not a big deal.

353
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:11,280
I read both your

354
00:21:11,280 --> 00:21:12,240
and Gu Yan's updates.

355
00:21:12,760 --> 00:21:13,800
Anyone can tell at a glance

356
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:14,960
that yours is better.

357
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:17,480
It was Gu Yan himself
who threw a tantrum

358
00:21:17,480 --> 00:21:18,555
and refused to update.

359
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:20,040
You stepped in to help him.

360
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:21,920
Why should you be the one to give in?

361
00:21:25,440 --> 00:21:26,080
Have you eaten?

362
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:28,120
Getting angry on an empty stomach

363
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:29,040
only makes it worse.

364
00:21:29,888 --> 00:21:31,066
I am too angry to feel hungry.

365
00:21:31,360 --> 00:21:32,240
I am hungry.

366
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:34,000
Just come eat with me.

367
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:35,680
Come on.

368
00:21:40,960 --> 00:21:41,640
Try this.

369
00:21:42,044 --> 00:21:43,120
This one is really good, too.

370
00:21:43,120 --> 00:21:44,066
I will get you some.

371
00:21:44,555 --> 00:21:45,320
I will do it myself.

372
00:21:46,120 --> 00:21:46,720
Here, let me.

373
00:21:58,920 --> 00:22:00,720
Want to eat somewhere else, Mr. He Han?

374
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:02,480
It is fine.

375
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:07,960
Mr. He Han, Zhangzhu,

376
00:22:08,155 --> 00:22:09,022
what a coincidence.

377
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:12,000
Hello, Ms. Lin.

378
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:23,360
Try this, too.

379
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:24,880
You have not had this.

380
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:27,200
It is their signature dish.

381
00:22:27,320 --> 00:22:28,333
Braised beef short ribs.

382
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:30,320
I heard it takes eight hours to cook.

383
00:22:31,088 --> 00:22:32,400
- Give it a try.
- Order.

384
00:22:32,480 --> 00:22:32,880
Eat.

385
00:22:35,080 --> 00:22:36,080
During this time,

386
00:22:37,311 --> 00:22:39,022
even though I did not
submit on schedule,

387
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:41,400
I realized that when I
went into the mountains

388
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:42,200
and wrote there,

389
00:22:42,311 --> 00:22:44,333
I had a completely
different state of mind.

390
00:22:44,466 --> 00:22:45,480
And I felt very inspired.

391
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:48,080
Much better than sitting at home
and typing at a computer.

392
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:49,640
Actually, that place

393
00:22:49,640 --> 00:22:50,680
is not far from the city.

394
00:22:50,680 --> 00:22:51,800
Just one or two hours away.

395
00:22:52,560 --> 00:22:53,560
If you have time,

396
00:22:54,244 --> 00:22:55,200
you can go, too.

397
00:22:55,733 --> 00:22:57,400
- Then we could go together.
- Do you realize that not submitting it

398
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:58,977
has caused our boss a lot of trouble?

399
00:23:00,933 --> 00:23:02,140
I turned it in late this time.

400
00:23:02,320 --> 00:23:02,920
Sorry.

401
00:23:03,177 --> 00:23:05,120
- There were special circumstances...
- This is not something

402
00:23:05,120 --> 00:23:06,150
a simple apology can fix.

403
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:07,666
I have already apologized to Ms. Lin.

404
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:09,120
And I heard Dingqi Platform

405
00:23:09,120 --> 00:23:10,640
actually received the draft last night.

406
00:23:11,377 --> 00:23:12,844
I know it was not written by me.

407
00:23:13,088 --> 00:23:14,466
So there is only one possibility.

408
00:23:14,520 --> 00:23:15,600
Ms. Lin wrote it for me.

409
00:23:25,822 --> 00:23:27,080
- At that moment,
- No...

410
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:29,160
that was when I realized what Ms. Lin

411
00:23:29,160 --> 00:23:29,840
means to me.

412
00:23:30,720 --> 00:23:31,920
At a critical moment,

413
00:23:32,100 --> 00:23:33,630
she would still give everything for me.

414
00:23:36,177 --> 00:23:37,840
What if she did not write it for you?

415
00:23:42,640 --> 00:23:43,760
She definitely would.

416
00:23:44,440 --> 00:23:44,960
Why?

417
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:46,160
Because I heard

418
00:23:46,160 --> 00:23:47,720
that when you failed to submit,

419
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:49,120
Ms. Lin wrote it for you, too.

420
00:23:54,150 --> 00:23:55,440
I don't follow your logic.

421
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:56,760
So you

422
00:23:57,120 --> 00:23:58,720
were testing your editor,

423
00:23:58,800 --> 00:24:00,000
putting her to the test?

424
00:24:00,600 --> 00:24:02,520
That is a bit childish,
do you not think?

425
00:24:03,240 --> 00:24:04,240
I just wanted to be sure

426
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:06,155
that the person I work with,
the person I trust,

427
00:24:06,160 --> 00:24:07,040
will stand by me,

428
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:07,960
no matter what happens.

429
00:24:09,222 --> 00:24:10,511
Just as childish as expected.

430
00:24:10,911 --> 00:24:12,200
If you believe it, then believe it.

431
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:13,160
Why do you need proof?

432
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:15,160
Needing proof means you don't trust.

433
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:17,666
You got your proof this time,
but what about next time?

434
00:24:19,777 --> 00:24:21,444
There won't be a next time.

435
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:23,800
But why do I feel like

436
00:24:24,840 --> 00:24:26,360
Mr. He Han, the more you talk,

437
00:24:26,360 --> 00:24:28,360
the more it sounds like
you're trying to drive a wedge

438
00:24:28,377 --> 00:24:29,600
between Lin Zhanqiao and me?

439
00:24:32,760 --> 00:24:34,600
Or is it that deep down

440
00:24:34,880 --> 00:24:36,000
you hope she doesn't help me,

441
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:37,960
so I can be left on my own?

442
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:39,640
Whether she helps you or not,

443
00:24:39,933 --> 00:24:41,222
you'll fall apart anyway.

444
00:25:27,080 --> 00:25:27,840
Let me tell you!

445
00:25:28,044 --> 00:25:28,920
That update yesterday

446
00:25:28,920 --> 00:25:30,160
was not written by her.

447
00:25:30,160 --> 00:25:31,270
She didn't write it for you.

448
00:25:33,955 --> 00:25:35,400
Mr. He Han wrote it for you.

449
00:25:35,410 --> 00:25:36,960
And it's tonnes of times
better than yours.

450
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:38,160
Have you said enough, Zhangzhu?

451
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:43,000
Go back and reflect on
what you did today.

452
00:25:43,020 --> 00:25:45,355
Do not come to me again
until you have thought it through.

453
00:25:45,440 --> 00:25:46,840
I just told the truth.

454
00:25:46,840 --> 00:25:49,022
- Or it's not fair.
- Stop working at Chenxing anymore.

455
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:17,720
Zhangzhu.

456
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:21,040
Zhangzhu!

457
00:26:23,022 --> 00:26:23,960
Where are you going?

458
00:26:25,911 --> 00:26:27,920
I just couldn't stand
the way he talked to you.

459
00:26:30,760 --> 00:26:31,800
If I hadn't said it,

460
00:26:32,080 --> 00:26:34,080
and you and my boss hadn't said it,
he would've

461
00:26:34,080 --> 00:26:35,866
started thinking he's something special.

462
00:26:37,360 --> 00:26:38,120
Calm down first.

463
00:26:39,666 --> 00:26:41,680
Lin Zhanqiao must
have had no choice just now.

464
00:26:41,720 --> 00:26:43,666
That's why she said something so harsh.

465
00:26:44,044 --> 00:26:46,120
She didn't mean it.
Give her some time. It will pass.

466
00:26:48,320 --> 00:26:48,880
Stop crying.

467
00:26:49,177 --> 00:26:50,444
It's not that big of a deal.

468
00:26:50,488 --> 00:26:51,720
Let me go talk to her for you.

469
00:26:53,022 --> 00:26:53,880
Just leave me alone.

470
00:26:55,520 --> 00:26:56,560
When I said those things,

471
00:26:56,560 --> 00:26:58,880
I had already thought through
what the consequences would be.

472
00:27:01,640 --> 00:27:02,480
I won't regret it.

473
00:27:18,533 --> 00:27:20,355
I have already made arrangements.

474
00:27:21,800 --> 00:27:22,840
The overdue taxes

475
00:27:23,200 --> 00:27:24,720
under your company

476
00:27:25,200 --> 00:27:26,400
will all be covered by me.

477
00:27:26,911 --> 00:27:28,488
The past profits of the company

478
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:29,880
that belonged to you

479
00:27:30,640 --> 00:27:31,640
and should belong to you

480
00:27:31,920 --> 00:27:32,720
will remain yours.

481
00:27:35,355 --> 00:27:37,733
Will there be any other issues
that could involve me?

482
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:38,480
No.

483
00:27:39,520 --> 00:27:40,400
I'm not that foolish

484
00:27:41,400 --> 00:27:43,280
to break the law and drag you into it.

485
00:27:46,520 --> 00:27:48,755
So, what was the purpose of you
setting up this company?

486
00:27:50,320 --> 00:27:51,800
This year's profit

487
00:27:52,444 --> 00:27:54,377
is not a significant amount for you.

488
00:27:56,640 --> 00:27:57,480
I did it for you.

489
00:27:59,880 --> 00:28:01,240
So, you could have

490
00:28:01,240 --> 00:28:02,755
more funds at your own disposal,

491
00:28:02,822 --> 00:28:04,266
and that was my original intention.

492
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:08,760
I hoped you could live more freely.

493
00:28:09,800 --> 00:28:11,240
And I hoped that because of me,

494
00:28:11,720 --> 00:28:13,880
your life could
have a little more happiness.

495
00:28:15,240 --> 00:28:17,320
I know your parents' situation

496
00:28:17,480 --> 00:28:18,800
has always troubled you.

497
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:21,800
Other than legal means,

498
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:23,480
I don't know what else I can do.

499
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:25,680
So, from another perspective,

500
00:28:26,360 --> 00:28:27,800
having more financial freedom

501
00:28:28,480 --> 00:28:29,680
might help you

502
00:28:30,244 --> 00:28:32,111
come to terms
with yourself a little more.

503
00:28:41,240 --> 00:28:41,640
Then,

504
00:28:44,360 --> 00:28:46,120
aside from this company,

505
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:48,760
do you have any others outside?

506
00:28:49,400 --> 00:28:50,000
No.

507
00:28:51,640 --> 00:28:53,960
Lawyers are not allowed
to engage in business activities.

508
00:28:55,466 --> 00:28:56,977
I wouldn't dare go that far.

509
00:29:01,520 --> 00:29:03,160
Once everything is settled,

510
00:29:04,560 --> 00:29:05,600
shut the company down.

511
00:29:08,880 --> 00:29:10,000
I'm not with you for money.

512
00:29:12,680 --> 00:29:13,840
I can earn my own living.

513
00:29:15,200 --> 00:29:16,911
Even if I don't make as much as you,

514
00:29:17,280 --> 00:29:18,160
it's enough.

515
00:29:20,480 --> 00:29:21,920
Since Zhang Yousen could find out

516
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:23,955
about the connection
between this company and us,

517
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:26,200
others can too.

518
00:29:29,120 --> 00:29:30,640
I don't want our relationship

519
00:29:31,080 --> 00:29:32,800
to cause you trouble in any way.

520
00:29:35,600 --> 00:29:36,560
Even in the worst case,

521
00:29:37,320 --> 00:29:38,920
if rumors spread and people find out,

522
00:29:40,333 --> 00:29:42,688
being exposed for love
is still better than for money.

523
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:53,640
If Zhang Yousen really marries you,

524
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:56,440
I will feel terrible.

525
00:30:22,866 --> 00:30:24,844
What did you want
to see me about just now?

526
00:30:25,120 --> 00:30:26,200
I wanted to remind you

527
00:30:27,240 --> 00:30:28,720
to avoid risks in advance.

528
00:30:29,080 --> 00:30:29,920
If possible,

529
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:31,520
change the legal representative.

530
00:30:32,120 --> 00:30:33,377
Otherwise, once this matter

531
00:30:33,680 --> 00:30:34,560
gets investigated,

532
00:30:34,720 --> 00:30:35,600
it will be serious.

533
00:30:36,280 --> 00:30:37,560
At best, financial loss.

534
00:30:37,840 --> 00:30:39,720
At worst, you could
be listed as untrustworthy.

535
00:30:41,240 --> 00:30:42,120
You met Lawyer Bei?

536
00:30:42,888 --> 00:30:44,311
What did he tell you?

537
00:30:47,733 --> 00:30:49,760
That depends on whether you
believe him or believe me.

538
00:31:19,740 --> 00:31:21,100
(Keeping stories alive together.)

539
00:31:33,960 --> 00:31:34,480
What is it?

540
00:31:34,920 --> 00:31:35,480
I don't know.

541
00:31:39,622 --> 00:31:41,377
Was it really He Han
who wrote it for me?

542
00:31:42,422 --> 00:31:43,911
Where is the draft? I want to see it.

543
00:31:44,200 --> 00:31:45,822
I already deleted his version.

544
00:31:45,933 --> 00:31:47,630
If you don't give it to me,
I'll ask Zhangzhu.

545
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:49,977
Dingqi Platform also received my draft.
They must still have it.

546
00:31:50,120 --> 00:31:50,800
Do not look at it.

547
00:31:50,933 --> 00:31:52,270
Yours is the one that was submitted.

548
00:31:52,280 --> 00:31:53,777
What is the point of looking at his?

549
00:31:54,600 --> 00:31:56,200
Besides, it was only
a temporary measure.

550
00:31:56,288 --> 00:31:57,577
He helped out in an emergency.

551
00:31:57,680 --> 00:32:00,120
Now that yours has been submitted,
his version is no longer needed.

552
00:32:00,133 --> 00:32:01,644
What is the point of looking at it?

553
00:32:02,400 --> 00:32:04,288
Was it you who asked He Han to write it?

554
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:05,280
No.

555
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:08,040
He volunteered?

556
00:32:09,680 --> 00:32:10,720
Was he thinking about you,

557
00:32:10,920 --> 00:32:12,160
or just being kind, or...

558
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:13,600
Or did he have other motives?

559
00:32:13,600 --> 00:32:15,320
What other motives could he have?

560
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:18,160
No matter the reason,

561
00:32:18,160 --> 00:32:19,977
at the last moment,
he helped you write it

562
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:21,311
to help us get through it,

563
00:32:21,920 --> 00:32:23,120
so I should be thanking him.

564
00:32:24,088 --> 00:32:25,120
You did not know before.

565
00:32:25,320 --> 00:32:26,120
Now that you know,

566
00:32:26,120 --> 00:32:27,280
you should thank him as well,

567
00:32:27,520 --> 00:32:28,640
instead of standing here,

568
00:32:28,760 --> 00:32:30,360
questioning his intentions.

569
00:32:30,360 --> 00:32:32,000
The outline for Drunk Old Friend

570
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:33,080
was drafted by He Han.

571
00:32:33,311 --> 00:32:34,600
You handed it to me to write.

572
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:36,311
Now that readers are responding so well,

573
00:32:36,360 --> 00:32:38,666
I don't believe he is generous enough
to be happy about it.

574
00:32:38,670 --> 00:32:39,955
But the copyright is with me.

575
00:32:40,080 --> 00:32:41,960
When he left, I paid him.

576
00:32:42,960 --> 00:32:43,640
Besides, Gu Yan,

577
00:32:44,480 --> 00:32:46,560
his reason for helping us

578
00:32:46,866 --> 00:32:48,200
is a separate matter.

579
00:32:49,560 --> 00:32:50,480
Other than Zhangzhu,

580
00:32:51,680 --> 00:32:52,840
does Dingqi Platform also know

581
00:32:52,840 --> 00:32:53,866
that he wrote it for me?

582
00:32:54,120 --> 00:32:55,640
Do others at Chenxing know?

583
00:32:55,840 --> 00:32:56,680
No one knows.

584
00:32:57,560 --> 00:32:58,400
I believe

585
00:32:58,400 --> 00:33:00,280
no one else knows about this.

586
00:33:00,511 --> 00:33:01,280
That is impossible.

587
00:33:01,720 --> 00:33:02,840
Zhangzhu will say something.

588
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:04,440
She always stands up for He Han.

589
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:06,040
Have you said enough?

590
00:33:07,040 --> 00:33:08,000
In this matter,

591
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:08,880
you have no right

592
00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:10,480
to doubt or accuse anyone,

593
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:13,200
whether it is He Han, Zhangzhu, or me.

594
00:33:13,466 --> 00:33:15,160
You know where the responsibility lies.

595
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:16,960
You should also know I would write it.

596
00:33:17,680 --> 00:33:18,880
Drunk Old Friend means more

597
00:33:18,880 --> 00:33:20,000
to me than anything.

598
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:21,200
Then, what are you doing here?

599
00:33:21,320 --> 00:33:23,444
What are you trying to prove
by dragging everyone into this?

600
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:29,240
Because you have always
made everyone feel

601
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:31,720
that He Han is the most important person

602
00:33:31,800 --> 00:33:32,760
in your world.

603
00:33:33,600 --> 00:33:35,240
When you attended events with me,

604
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:37,160
in all the event photos,

605
00:33:37,160 --> 00:33:38,960
there was not
a single picture of you and me.

606
00:33:39,840 --> 00:33:40,320
Why?

607
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:43,800
Because you were always with He Han.

608
00:33:44,666 --> 00:33:46,360
You even forgot you went there with me.

609
00:33:46,360 --> 00:33:47,711
I went to look for you that day.

610
00:33:47,822 --> 00:33:49,000
I searched the whole venue,

611
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:50,320
inside and out,

612
00:33:50,320 --> 00:33:51,640
but I could not find you.

613
00:33:52,933 --> 00:33:54,120
I could not just stand there

614
00:33:54,120 --> 00:33:56,111
a meter away
from you two like a fool, right?

615
00:33:56,688 --> 00:33:58,911
You looked like you
had endless things to talk about.

616
00:33:59,160 --> 00:34:00,777
There were so many people that day.

617
00:34:01,440 --> 00:34:02,680
I had my own plans.

618
00:34:03,320 --> 00:34:04,200
But no matter what,

619
00:34:04,440 --> 00:34:06,760
it was never my intention to ignore you,

620
00:34:06,760 --> 00:34:08,160
let alone embarrass you.

621
00:34:08,920 --> 00:34:09,920
But even so,

622
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:11,960
that and you disappearing
or not submitting the draft

623
00:34:12,080 --> 00:34:13,290
are still two separate matters.

624
00:34:13,440 --> 00:34:14,511
You should not use...

625
00:34:17,422 --> 00:34:18,711
What are you trying to say?

626
00:34:19,888 --> 00:34:22,311
You shouldn't use Zhao Lanxin
to threaten Chenxing and me.

627
00:34:22,760 --> 00:34:23,480
Who told you that?

628
00:34:23,600 --> 00:34:24,644
No one needed to tell me.

629
00:34:24,650 --> 00:34:27,022
This is the most sensitive issue for me
as someone in the same field.

630
00:34:27,040 --> 00:34:28,880
She did talk to me a lot,

631
00:34:28,880 --> 00:34:30,600
but I did not agree to anything.

632
00:34:30,610 --> 00:34:31,400
You have to trust me.

633
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:33,040
Alright, enough. Stop talking, okay?

634
00:34:33,200 --> 00:34:34,040
On this matter,

635
00:34:34,288 --> 00:34:36,080
for both you and me,
this is the last time.

636
00:34:36,880 --> 00:34:37,880
If there is a next time,

637
00:34:37,960 --> 00:34:38,920
and within half an hour
before the deadline,

638
00:34:38,920 --> 00:34:40,270
I still don't see your manuscript,

639
00:34:40,280 --> 00:34:41,630
I'll immediately
inform Dingqi Platform

640
00:34:41,640 --> 00:34:43,666
to permanently stop updates
for Drunk Old Friend.

641
00:34:43,844 --> 00:34:45,920
There will no longer
be a whole office waiting for you.

642
00:34:45,920 --> 00:34:48,070
No one will write for you,
and no one will cover for you.

643
00:34:48,080 --> 00:34:49,190
He Han will not. I will not.

644
00:34:49,200 --> 00:34:49,880
No one will.

645
00:34:53,120 --> 00:34:54,360
You cannot stop the updates.

646
00:34:55,120 --> 00:34:55,880
Then, try me.

647
00:35:51,680 --> 00:35:52,040
Hello.

648
00:35:53,920 --> 00:35:55,400
Do not blame Zhangzhu for today.

649
00:35:55,933 --> 00:35:58,360
She is young and impulsive.
Everyone has been through that.

650
00:35:59,040 --> 00:36:00,480
Just scare her a little.

651
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:01,920
Do not really fire her.

652
00:36:03,440 --> 00:36:04,440
I know how to handle it.

653
00:36:05,680 --> 00:36:07,200
But this is not just about today.

654
00:36:08,160 --> 00:36:09,960
The company has its own rules.

655
00:36:10,440 --> 00:36:11,960
She cannot run to you for everything

656
00:36:11,960 --> 00:36:12,880
or tell you everything.

657
00:36:13,520 --> 00:36:14,040
Yes,

658
00:36:14,511 --> 00:36:15,960
I understand that you are her idol,

659
00:36:16,080 --> 00:36:17,800
but she cannot tell you everything.

660
00:36:18,680 --> 00:36:20,200
I have reminded her many times before,

661
00:36:20,320 --> 00:36:22,240
but she never took it seriously.

662
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:23,440
If I still

663
00:36:23,680 --> 00:36:24,920
do nothing after today,

664
00:36:25,440 --> 00:36:27,480
she will only become more reckless.

665
00:36:28,040 --> 00:36:28,960
Yes, I understand.

666
00:36:29,960 --> 00:36:31,520
But every time she came to me,

667
00:36:31,520 --> 00:36:32,600
it was because of you.

668
00:36:33,080 --> 00:36:34,200
She is not chasing an idol.

669
00:36:34,200 --> 00:36:35,320
She saw you were in trouble

670
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:36,480
and came to me for help.

671
00:36:36,640 --> 00:36:38,200
What happened today was an accident.

672
00:36:38,440 --> 00:36:40,200
And the one being reckless is Gu Yan,

673
00:36:40,200 --> 00:36:40,880
not Zhangzhu.

674
00:36:40,880 --> 00:36:42,600
Yes, as a friend, she is great.

675
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:45,000
But as my assistant,
that is not acceptable.

676
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:47,040
And she should not,
nor does she need to,

677
00:36:47,040 --> 00:36:48,760
let Gu Yan know so much.

678
00:36:52,333 --> 00:36:53,488
Have you been drinking?

679
00:36:53,680 --> 00:36:54,280
No.

680
00:36:55,280 --> 00:36:56,400
Setting Zhangzhu aside,

681
00:36:56,880 --> 00:36:57,880
Lin Zhanqiao, why did you

682
00:36:58,040 --> 00:36:59,520
pull the version I wrote?

683
00:37:00,400 --> 00:37:01,360
What were you thinking?

684
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:03,600
You also thought my version was better,

685
00:37:03,600 --> 00:37:04,120
didn't you?

686
00:37:04,280 --> 00:37:05,555
Then, why did you publish his?

687
00:37:06,200 --> 00:37:08,160
He submitted late,
and it was nothing special.

688
00:37:08,320 --> 00:37:10,400
If you had used mine,
he would have fallen in line.

689
00:37:10,400 --> 00:37:12,160
By using his, you are just enabling him.

690
00:37:12,160 --> 00:37:12,800
Come on.

691
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:15,520
You're constantly
pretending to be serious

692
00:37:15,520 --> 00:37:17,200
and rational, acting all high-minded.

693
00:37:17,210 --> 00:37:18,960
You can't even tell
genuine from fake emotions

694
00:37:18,960 --> 00:37:20,120
or understand people properly.

695
00:37:20,160 --> 00:37:22,555
Lin Zhanqiao, you don't deserve
for others to treat you well.

696
00:38:15,880 --> 00:38:16,960
Can you stop following me?

697
00:38:17,030 --> 00:38:18,520
I am worried you will go buy alcohol.

698
00:38:18,520 --> 00:38:20,080
I am, but that is none of your concern.

699
00:38:20,080 --> 00:38:21,720
From now on,
I won't care about you anymore.

700
00:38:21,730 --> 00:38:22,760
So, you don't have to worry

701
00:38:22,760 --> 00:38:24,222
about whether I drink or not.

702
00:38:24,333 --> 00:38:26,200
We have said things
like this more than once.

703
00:38:26,200 --> 00:38:27,600
What is the point?

704
00:38:28,640 --> 00:38:30,840
I still cannot just stand by
when you are drinking.

705
00:38:30,840 --> 00:38:32,240
Then, start now and do nothing.

706
00:38:32,520 --> 00:38:34,320
I will not bother you anymore.

707
00:38:34,822 --> 00:38:36,466
I have never said you were bothering me.

708
00:38:36,470 --> 00:38:37,840
I know you are trying to help me.

709
00:38:37,840 --> 00:38:38,720
Do you need it?

710
00:38:39,120 --> 00:38:41,000
You don't.
Because you are Lin Zhanqiao!

711
00:38:41,880 --> 00:38:43,560
You can live well without anyone.

712
00:38:43,840 --> 00:38:45,280
Because you are always the right one.

713
00:38:45,370 --> 00:38:46,555
When I drink myself senseless,

714
00:38:46,600 --> 00:38:48,040
you see it as escape, as weakness.

715
00:38:48,240 --> 00:38:49,640
You want everyone around you

716
00:38:49,640 --> 00:38:50,600
to be just like you,

717
00:38:50,800 --> 00:38:52,720
orderly, idealistic, and driven.

718
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:54,120
When they cannot be,

719
00:38:54,222 --> 00:38:55,080
you feel disappointed,

720
00:38:55,200 --> 00:38:56,400
like they are beyond saving.

721
00:38:56,800 --> 00:38:58,280
Do you know that sense of superiority

722
00:38:58,400 --> 00:38:59,440
is very off-putting?

723
00:39:00,200 --> 00:39:01,420
It is not that you dislike it.

724
00:39:01,420 --> 00:39:03,440
You are afraid.
You actually dislike yourself.

725
00:39:03,440 --> 00:39:04,790
Just like your father dislikes you.

726
00:39:04,911 --> 00:39:06,520
So you have never wanted to get better.

727
00:39:06,720 --> 00:39:07,800
Because the moment you do,

728
00:39:07,800 --> 00:39:09,120
you lose to him.

729
00:39:09,160 --> 00:39:09,640
Yes!

730
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:10,760
At least, let me finish.

731
00:39:12,080 --> 00:39:14,280
That is why every time
I try to treat you well

732
00:39:14,280 --> 00:39:15,520
and hope you can become better,

733
00:39:15,520 --> 00:39:16,720
you will turn on me,

734
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:18,040
mock me, and blame me.

735
00:39:18,040 --> 00:39:19,680
Even what you said
just now was nonsense!

736
00:39:22,911 --> 00:39:24,760
Who is it
that does not deserve kindness?

737
00:39:24,800 --> 00:39:26,760
Who is it that doesn't
want others to treat him well?

738
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:27,760
It is you. It is He Han!

739
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:29,360
Yes! You are right about everything.

740
00:39:29,360 --> 00:39:30,400
You see everything clearly!

741
00:39:30,644 --> 00:39:32,280
But, Lin Zhanqiao, have you ever thought

742
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:34,200
that if you are really that strong

743
00:39:34,280 --> 00:39:35,160
and so clear-minded,

744
00:39:35,320 --> 00:39:36,840
after ten years together,

745
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:39,120
have I become better?

746
00:39:40,480 --> 00:39:42,240
Do you really think you can help me?

747
00:39:48,720 --> 00:39:49,520
Since we

748
00:39:50,160 --> 00:39:51,080
dislike each other

749
00:39:51,120 --> 00:39:52,680
and can never change each other,

750
00:39:53,440 --> 00:39:55,160
let me disappear from your sight.

751
00:39:55,688 --> 00:39:56,880
You will see whether I care.

752
00:39:57,880 --> 00:39:58,240
Fine.

753
00:39:59,533 --> 00:40:01,133
Don't come looking for me again.

754
00:40:01,360 --> 00:40:02,360
Remember to do nothing.

755
00:40:06,280 --> 00:40:06,680
Go.

756
00:40:09,360 --> 00:40:09,920
Go!

757
00:41:06,430 --> 00:41:09,200
♪I keep asking myself♪

758
00:41:10,940 --> 00:41:14,260
♪What it is I should become♪

759
00:41:15,940 --> 00:41:25,200
♪To follow what my heart truly wants♪

760
00:41:33,640 --> 00:41:36,690
♪Like a drifting dandelion♪

761
00:41:38,300 --> 00:41:41,380
♪Turning where it drifts♪

762
00:41:42,310 --> 00:41:47,430
♪Into soil where it can grow♪

763
00:41:49,370 --> 00:41:52,230
♪When the rain comes, I hide♪

764
00:41:52,940 --> 00:41:56,020
♪In a flower shop at the corner♪

765
00:41:56,650 --> 00:42:02,180
♪Even spring borrows its fragrance♪

766
00:42:04,010 --> 00:42:10,260
♪Moonlight keeps me company
on lonely roads♪

767
00:42:11,180 --> 00:42:17,390
♪Across fields of blooms,
a boat awaits me♪

768
00:42:18,260 --> 00:42:25,010
♪Swaying in the shape of the wind♪

769
00:42:25,700 --> 00:42:30,270
♪Not waiting for calm to come♪

770
00:42:33,040 --> 00:42:35,770
♪I want to go on like this♪

771
00:42:37,860 --> 00:42:40,770
♪Moving forward, not alone♪

772
00:42:41,530 --> 00:42:47,960
♪This moment is worth
more than anything♪

773
00:42:48,690 --> 00:42:50,450
♪No need to define the distance♪

774
00:42:50,450 --> 00:42:55,380
♪Let trials become my scenery♪

775
00:42:56,270 --> 00:43:01,820
♪A life not yet full begins again♪

776
00:43:05,921 --> 00:43:07,041
(I've been thinking.)

777
00:43:08,321 --> 00:43:11,601
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

778
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:19,691
(is probably different.)

779
00:43:20,691 --> 00:43:22,441
♪If the sky♪

780
00:43:22,951 --> 00:43:24,351
♪And the sea♪

781
00:43:24,891 --> 00:43:26,601
♪Turned upside down♪

782
00:43:28,161 --> 00:43:30,091
♪If a swimming fish♪

783
00:43:30,491 --> 00:43:33,881
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

784
00:43:35,651 --> 00:43:37,621
♪If back then♪

785
00:43:37,981 --> 00:43:42,391
♪We had never let go♪

786
00:43:42,991 --> 00:43:49,271
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

787
00:43:50,391 --> 00:43:52,541
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

788
00:43:52,541 --> 00:43:54,411
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

789
00:43:54,591 --> 00:43:57,031
♪And found our way back whole♪

790
00:43:57,871 --> 00:44:00,041
♪So let this surging love♪

791
00:44:00,041 --> 00:44:04,471
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

792
00:44:05,371 --> 00:44:07,551
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

793
00:44:07,551 --> 00:44:08,641
♪That's alright♪

794
00:44:09,181 --> 00:44:09,931
♪If we're buried♪

795
00:44:09,931 --> 00:44:12,631
♪By passing years all the better♪

796
00:44:12,891 --> 00:44:15,071
♪At least we still can keep♪

797
00:44:15,251 --> 00:44:19,671
♪This one eternal photograph♪

798
00:44:35,431 --> 00:44:37,721
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

799
00:44:37,721 --> 00:44:39,481
♪Running in opposite ways♪

800
00:44:39,601 --> 00:44:42,071
♪Searching all along the way♪

801
00:44:42,871 --> 00:44:45,031
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

802
00:44:45,221 --> 00:44:50,131
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

803
00:44:50,131 --> 00:44:53,651
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

804
00:44:53,891 --> 00:44:54,861
♪Only after loss♪

805
00:44:54,861 --> 00:44:57,491
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

806
00:44:57,901 --> 00:45:00,261
♪In another time and space♪

807
00:45:00,261 --> 00:45:01,821
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

808
00:45:01,821 --> 00:45:04,651
♪Till we grow old♪

809
00:45:05,611 --> 00:45:07,901
♪But still the sky will never♪

810
00:45:07,901 --> 00:45:10,571
♪Turn with the sea♪

811
00:45:13,091 --> 00:45:15,501
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

812
00:45:15,501 --> 00:45:20,711
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪
